                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1232">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/178d</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Hale</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-27T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Press reports state that Costa Rica has instituted suit against Nicaragua before
                    Central American Court of Justice on the ground that the Canal Treaty between
                    Nicaragua and the United States constitutes a violation of Costa Rica’s
                    rights.</p>
                <p>Report by cable present status and developments as they occur, keeping Legation
                    Managua fully informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
